/--
Suppose `f` is holomorphic on a neighborhood of the closed unit disk and `f 0 ‚â† 0`.
Then there exists a constant `C` such that for all `m : ‚Ñï` and `|z| ‚â§ 1`,

  |1 - ‚àë_{k=0}^m f^{(k)}(0)/(k! * f(0)) * z^k| ‚â§ C * |z|^(m+1).

This is stated here assuming analyticity on some open ball of radius `R > 1` around `0`.
-/
theorem jirilebl_ca_ca_12556 (f : ‚ÑÇ ‚Üí ‚ÑÇ) (R : ‚Ñù) (hR : 1 < R)
  (h_analytic : AnalyticOn ‚ÑÇ f (ball (0 : ‚ÑÇ) R)) (h0 : f 0 ‚â† 0) :
  ‚àÉ C : ‚Ñù, ‚àÄ (m : ‚Ñï) (z : ‚ÑÇ), abs z ‚â§ 1 ‚Üí
    abs (1 - ‚àë k in range (m + 1), (Function.iterate deriv k f) 0 / ((‚Üë(Nat.factorial k) : ‚ÑÇ) * f 0) * z ^ k)
      ‚â§ C * (abs z) ^ (m + 1) := by
